fields.description:
While working on upgrading the CentOS 5 and 6 images on eustore, I noticed that euca-get-console-output doesn't work with CentOS 5/6 images.  I did some research and made sure that I updated grub.conf to have the /dev/ttyS0, updated /etc/inittab and updated /etc/securetty.  After rebooting the instance, still no joy.  The instance has virtio_console enabled as well. 

{code}
-bash-3.2# lsmod | grep virtio
virtio_console         50681  0
virtio_balloon         41025  0
virtio_pci             43593  0
virtio_ring            37953  1 virtio_pci
virtio_net             48577  0
virtio_blk             42441  4
virtio                 39365  5 virtio_console,virtio_balloon,virtio_pci,virtio_net,virtio_blk
{code}

This should be fixed in commit 5a23f29, which switches the default encoding to UTF-8 and replaces un-decodable characters with placeholders.

If the console output isn't UTF-8 or ASCII, use the new {{--encoding}} option to select another character encoding.

Based on feedback from [~shaon] I tweaked the fix rather substantially.  Instead of assuming UTF-8 unless instructed otherwise, the command now automatically detects the encoding to use based on the environment.  To change the encoding, use the LC_CTYPE environment variable.
